List Methods that modify in place (return None)

⚠️ Do not assign them to variables!
--------------------------------------

list.sort() → sorts the list in place (ascending by default)

list.reverse() → reverses the list in place

list.clear() → removes all elements (list becomes empty)

list.append(x) → adds a single element at the end

list.extend(iterable) → adds multiple elements at the end

list.insert(i, x) → inserts at a specific index

list.remove(x) → removes the first occurrence of x

list.pop(i) → removes and returns the element at index i (default last one)


List Methods that return a value
------------------------------------

These you can safely assign to variables.

len(list) → length of list

sum(list) → sum of elements

min(list) / max(list) → smallest / largest element

list.copy() → returns a shallow copy

list.count(x) → returns how many times x occurs

list.index(x) → returns the first index of x

sorted(list) → returns a new sorted list (does not modify original)

reversed(list) → returns an iterator (you can convert to list)
